    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-11-18T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-11-18T12:00:00-05:00" n="868"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d868">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BC Indonesia/11–1847: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Consulate General at Batavia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-11-18T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 18, 1947—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>316. No. 19 for Graham. Reurtel 25<note n="48" xml:id="d868fn48">See telegram
                        453, November 13, <ref target="#pg_1070">p. 1070</ref>.</note> Dept’s views
                    re question withdrawal forces follow: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Penultimate para resolution Nov 1 does not require any
                            withdrawals.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Last para resolution Nov 1 contemplates parties may agree to
                            withdrawals as part workable arrangement to implement cease fire.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> may work out with parties such an
                            arrangement.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Dept in general agreement with other views <gloss target="#t_urtel1"
                        >urtel</gloss> 25 except we consider proper meaning “occupied” (<gloss
                        target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> para 6<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) is
                    “control” and prefer alternative definition “control” contained <gloss
                        target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> para 6(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>).</p>
                <p>For your <gloss target="#t_Info1">info</gloss> last para resolution Nov 1
                    proposed in subcom by Belgian representative <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>
                    with concurrence Netherlands Representative.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
